name: AzureRedis
help: Manage dedicated Redis caches for your Azure applications.

properties.name: Location
properties.help: Location. Values from: `az account list-locations`. You can configure the default location using `az configure --defaults location=&lt;location&gt;`.

properties.name: Name
properties.help: Name of the Redis cache.

properties.name: ResourceGroup
properties.help: Name of resource group. You can configure the default group using `az configure --defaults group=&lt;name&gt;`.

properties.name: Sku
properties.help: Type of Redis cache.

properties.name: VmSize
properties.help: Size of Redis cache to deploy. Basic and Standard Cache sizes start with C. Premium Cache sizes start with P.

properties.name: EnableNonSslPort
properties.help: If the value is true, then the non-ssl redis server port (6379) will be enabled.

properties.name: MinimumTlsVersion
properties.help: Specifies the TLS version required by clients to connect to cache.

properties.name: RedisConfiguration
properties.help: JSON encoded configuration settings. Use @{file} to load from a file.

properties.name: ShardCount
properties.help: The number of shards to be created on a Premium Cluster Cache.

properties.name: StaticIp
properties.help: Specify a static ip if required for the VNET. If you do not specify a static IP then an IP address is chosen automatically.

properties.name: SubnetId
properties.help: The full resource ID of a subnet in a virtual network to deploy the redis cache in. Example format /subscriptions/{subid}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/Microsoft.{Network|ClassicNetwork}/VirtualNetworks/vnet1/subnets/subnet1.

properties.name: Tags
properties.help: Space-separated tags in 'key[=value]' format. Use "" to clear existing tags.

properties.name: TenantSettings
properties.help: Space-separated tenant settings in key[=value] format.

properties.name: Zones
properties.help: Space-separated list of availability zones into which to provision the resource.

properties.name: Subscription
properties.help: Name or ID of subscription. You can configure the default subscription using `az account set -s NAME_OR_ID`.
